text: Henry Trenchard (c. 1652 – 2 October 1694), of Lytchett Matravers, Dorset, was an English politician. He was a Member of Parliament (MP) for Poole in March 1679, October 1679, 1681 and 1689.http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1660-1690/member/trenchard- henry-1652-94 ==References== Category:1652 births Category:1694 deaths Category:People from Dorset Category:English MPs 1679 Category:English MPs 1681 Category:English MPs 1689–1690
